annotationA: Proteasome subunit alpha type-1; The proteasome is a multicatalytic proteinase complex which is characterized by its ability to cleave peptides with Arg, Phe, Tyr, Leu, and Glu adjacent to the leaving group at neutral or slightly basic pH. The proteasome has an ATP-dependent proteolytic activity; Belongs to the peptidase T1A family
annotationB: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 4 (Rpt4) is the 19S proteasomal ATPase, which is a component of the 26S proteosome complex. Rpt4 localizes to the nucleolus and participates in regulating rRNA transcription. Rpt4 physically interacts with the BHD tumor suppressor
